  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting and Protecting Older Women&#x2019;s Rights in Tanzania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Older Women</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sensitisation workshops on the rights of older women for 400 community leaders and public meetings in 10 villages | Training 3 local theatre groups to disseminate information on the rights of older men and women | 6 local and national campaigns to change attitutdes and legislation on rights and protection of older women | Training 240 community paralegals | Training 48 older women activists to document cases of rights violations to use in lobbying | Training 60 local and national media reps to contribute to raising public awareness on rights of older people | Supporting 64 local government leaders and 60 police and judicial officers to develop strategies to safeguard the rights of older women</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To promote and protect the rights of older women in Tanzania, who live in constant fear and frequently encounter extreme violence following claims of witchcraft practice.</narrative>
